				<li>"roof repair near me"</li>
				<li>"med spa in La Jolla"</li>
				<li>"best junk removal San Diego"</li>
			</ul>
			<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
				It's designed to capture nearby customers who are actively searching for what you offer.
			</p>
			<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
				<strong class="text-black">National SEO</strong>, on the other hand, targets broad, non-location-specific keywords like:
			</p>
			<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 space-y-2 ml-4">
				<li>"roof repair company"</li>
				<li>"junk removal services"</li>
				<li>"digital marketing agency"</li>
			</ul>
			<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
				It's built for companies competing across multiple states or nationwide.
			</p>
			<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
				Both matter ‚Äî but for most small and medium businesses, local SEO produces faster results with far less competition.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-black mb-4 mt-12 uppercase" style="font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif;">
				Why Local SEO Is Easier (and Smarter) to Win
			</h2>

			<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-4 mt-8" style="font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif;">
				1. Far Less Competition
			</h3>
			<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
				When you compete locally, you're up against a handful of businesses ‚Äî not thousands of nationwide competitors with massive ad budgets.
			</p>
			<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
				Ranking for "SEO services Los Angeles" might take months. Ranking for "SEO services Silver Lake" or "SEO agency Echo Park" can happen in weeks with focused optimization.
			</p>
			<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
				That's the difference precision makes.
			</p>

			<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-4 mt-8" style="font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif;">
				2. Google's Algorithm Favors Local Businesses
			</h3>
			<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
				Google prioritizes local intent. When someone searches "near me," the algorithm pushes verified, nearby businesses to the top ‚Äî often over larger national chains.
			</p>
			<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
				That means small, well-optimized local businesses can outperform national brands daily.
			</p>

			<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-4 mt-8" style="font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif;">
				3. Local SEO Converts Better
			</h3>
			<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
				Local searchers are closer to taking action.
			</p>
